textBeforeTable: The Texas A&M men earned their fourth title and first since 2001 last season. Texas also has four overall crowns, while the BU men lead the conference with seven championship trophies (2002-05, 2007-09). The Baylor women have won the past six postseason conference titles (2006-11). The Longhorn women hold the most wins overall with seven (1997-2002, '05). Oklahoma State was crowned in 2003, while Texas A&M won in 2004. The 3,000-seat center has 12 lighted courts, a special covered courtside seating area, locker rooms for both teams, coaches' offices, a training room and a players' lounge. The facility hosted NCAA Championships in 2002 and 2005 (men) and 2009 (men and women). The 2012 Big 12 Tennis Championships will be held at the George P. Mitchell Tennis Center in College Station, Texas from April 26-May 29. The Aggies have hosted the event on three additional occasions (1999, 2002, '08).
